<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Southern Ecuador and northern Peru, on mountain slopes between 1500 and 2000 m; known from one collection in each country and only one collection apart from the type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">PERU. Cajamarca</emphasis>
: Choropampa-Magdalena, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
A. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Sagástagui">Sagastagui</normalizedToken>
&amp; O. Tellez
</emphasis>
12708 (MO, HUT, FTG, NY).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">ECUADOR. Loja</emphasis>
: type collection.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Appears to be related to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nationis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea nationis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but sepals very unequal in size, the corolla tube shorter and all parts glabrous. The placement of this species is provisional.
</paragraph>
